This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 13, 2014, as Columbus Day in the United States. The proclamation acknowledges the impact of Christopher Columbus's historic voyage and his discovery of the New World. It also recognizes the contributions of Italian Americans and their descendants, who have shaped the country and served in various capacities, including the Armed Forces. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of celebrating the diverse history of the American continents and the commitment to strengthening the tribal sovereignty of Native Americans. It concludes by directing the display of the US flag on all public buildings on Columbus Day and encourages appropriate ceremonies and activities to observe the day.